00:18.134 --> 00:20.719
All right, what's going on?
What do you got?

00:20.721 --> 00:22.187
Angela Ferrara.
Called 911,

00:22.189 --> 00:23.326
said she was fighting
with her boyfriend.

00:23.351 --> 00:24.090
Uh-huh.

00:24.091 --> 00:26.274
When we got here,
she changed her story.

00:26.276 --> 00:27.943
Claims she fell down the stairs.
Really?

00:27.945 --> 00:28.927
Where's the boyfriend?

00:28.929 --> 00:29.928
No sign of him.

00:29.930 --> 00:31.730
Great. Angela...

00:31.732 --> 00:34.432
Detective Reagan. This is my
partner, Detective Curatola.

00:34.434 --> 00:36.034
You okay?
Yeah.

00:36.036 --> 00:39.237
I... My freakin' heel got
caught on one of the steps.

00:39.239 --> 00:41.573
- I just fell. It was...
- Right. We got

00:41.575 --> 00:43.458
a 911 call, said something
about your boyfriend.

00:43.460 --> 00:45.660
Oh, no, no.
That was a mistake.

00:45.662 --> 00:48.163
I-I kind of lost it
for a second.

00:48.165 --> 00:50.449
I'm so sorry to bother you guys.

00:50.451 --> 00:52.084
Where's your
boyfriend now?

00:52.086 --> 00:54.252
He took off a little while ago.

00:54.254 --> 00:55.787
He didn't have anything
to do with this.

00:55.789 --> 00:57.756
You understand, Angela,
there's only so much we can do

00:57.758 --> 01:00.142
to help you if you don't tell us
what really happened, all right?

01:00.144 --> 01:03.812
Yeah, no.
Like I said, I fell.

01:03.814 --> 01:06.298
Right.
I'm really sorry to bother you guys.

01:06.300 --> 01:07.516
I'm fine, really.

01:07.518 --> 01:09.351
Yeah, okay. No problem.
Thank you.

01:09.353 --> 01:11.236
We should
get her to the E.R.

01:11.238 --> 01:12.971
Yeah, you do that.
Right.

01:14.490 --> 01:17.142
What is with these girls?
Do they all use "I fell

01:17.144 --> 01:19.027
down the steps" for an excuse?
I don't know.

01:19.029 --> 01:21.980
They keep covering for
these sons of bitches.

01:21.982 --> 01:24.032
This is the next-door neighbor.
Do you have any idea

01:24.034 --> 01:26.451
what happened tonight, ma'am?
Well, Angela's a nice girl,

01:26.453 --> 01:28.587
but her tastin men
is the worst.

01:28.589 --> 01:30.972
Did you see her fight with her boyfriend?
No, I heard.

01:30.974 --> 01:33.825
We share the same bedroom wall.
I could write a book.

01:33.827 --> 01:35.544
Oh?
This is not the first time.

01:35.546 --> 01:36.545
Angela had

01:36.547 --> 01:38.346
a bad breakup

01:38.348 --> 01:39.497
with a Kevin.
Kevin.

01:39.499 --> 01:41.216
Yeah, I think he lives
on the block.

01:41.218 --> 01:44.335
Do you know the last name
on this Kevin guy?

01:44.337 --> 01:45.720
That's him.

01:45.722 --> 01:47.272
That's-that's
the Kevin.

01:47.274 --> 01:48.506
That's the Kevin?
Yeah.

01:48.508 --> 01:49.891
That's him.
Yeah.

01:49.893 --> 01:51.476
Okay.

01:52.361 --> 01:54.156
Kev, I need to ask
a few questions.

01:54.157 --> 01:55.186
I got nothing to say.

01:55.211 --> 01:57.301
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa,
we didn't ask you

01:57.401 --> 01:59.935
any questions yet-- how do you
know you got nothing to say?

01:59.937 --> 02:01.386
What's your full name, Kevin?

02:01.388 --> 02:02.354
Kevin Carr.

02:02.356 --> 02:03.388
Kevin Carr.
Kevin Carr.

02:03.390 --> 02:04.722
Do you know
Angela Ferrara?

02:04.724 --> 02:05.841
Yeah, so what?

02:05.843 --> 02:07.559
So what? So she got
hurt this evening.

02:07.561 --> 02:09.060
Do you know anything about that?
Nope.

02:09.062 --> 02:10.277
I don't date
Angela anymore.

02:10.280 --> 02:11.663
And unless you're
gonna arrest me,

02:11.665 --> 02:14.166
you got no right to keep me here.
Whoa. Kevin knows

02:14.168 --> 02:16.201
his rights.
 Yeah, sounds like you been

02:16.203 --> 02:18.420
in the system before, Kevin.
Maybe we should look you up.

02:18.422 --> 02:20.071
I'm not looking for trouble, all right?
Good.

02:20.073 --> 02:22.090
Then you won't mind coming down,
answering some questions.

02:22.092 --> 02:23.408
Let's go.
Oh, come on.

02:23.410 --> 02:25.076
Come on.

02:26.912 --> 02:29.047
Watch your head.

02:37.690 --> 02:41.526
Excuse me, I'm looking
for a patient, Angela Ferrara.

02:41.528 --> 02:44.062
I need to ask her a few questions.
Sorry, Detective,

02:44.064 --> 02:46.097
your questions are
gonna have to wait.

02:46.099 --> 02:49.100
Oh, well, okay,
then, Nurse.

02:50.069 --> 02:52.287
Can I have a kiss?
I don't know.

02:52.289 --> 02:53.538
Is it an emergency?
It is.

02:53.540 --> 02:54.823
Oh, okay.

02:54.825 --> 02:56.408
The boys with Henry?

02:56.410 --> 02:58.577
Yeah, I'm gonna pick 'em up
on the way home.

02:58.579 --> 03:00.912
You working all night tonight?
Yep.

03:00.914 --> 03:02.113
Covering for a girl.

03:02.115 --> 03:04.282
She's still on vacation
for the next few days.

03:04.284 --> 03:05.500
I see.

03:05.502 --> 03:06.718
Two weeks back,
and you already

03:06.720 --> 03:08.119
got the graveyard shift
in the E.R., huh?

03:08.121 --> 03:10.005
They're just throwing you
right in the deep end.

03:10.007 --> 03:11.806
Yeah, but I can handle it.

03:11.808 --> 03:14.292
Listen, I gotta go.
Yeah,

03:14.294 --> 03:16.094
but I need to speak
to Angela Ferrara.

03:16.096 --> 03:18.480
Can you help me out?
She's sleeping. Can't it wait till tomorrow?

03:18.482 --> 03:19.965
I guess so.
Did you take care of her?

03:19.967 --> 03:21.234
Yeah, she got knocked
around pretty good.

03:21.259 --> 03:22.301
Yeah, she did.

03:22.302 --> 03:24.636
And it wasn't by a flight of stairs.
Yeah. I didn't think so.

03:24.638 --> 03:25.854
Did you get the guy?
No.

03:25.856 --> 03:27.606
Her ex-boyfriend said
he wasn't with her tonight.

03:27.608 --> 03:30.308
Of course he did.
I gotta go. - Yeah.

03:30.310 --> 03:32.360
Oh, wait, can you go
to the market tomorrow?

03:32.362 --> 03:34.663
I got to go get a bunch
of stuff that we need.

03:34.665 --> 03:36.164
Yeah, I got it.
Don't worry about it.

03:36.166 --> 03:37.749
But use the coupons this time.
I got it.

03:37.751 --> 03:40.585
I'll use the coupons.
Okay. Bye.

03:42.088 --> 03:44.339
This just keeps getting
better and better.

03:53.266 --> 03:54.716
Gentlemen.

03:54.718 --> 03:55.884
Sir.

03:57.836 --> 03:59.271
How much longer?

03:59.273 --> 04:01.139
We've only been
here 20 minutes.

04:01.141 --> 04:02.724
Twenty-three.

04:02.726 --> 04:04.059
Commissioner.

04:04.061 --> 04:06.528
Hey! Good to see you, Sam.

04:06.530 --> 04:07.862
It's the mayor's
pet charity.

04:07.864 --> 04:09.864
Yet somehow I do not
see the mayor.

04:09.866 --> 04:12.534
Lovely to see you, Frank.

04:12.536 --> 04:14.069
You're looking
lovely, Maryanne.

04:14.071 --> 04:17.021
Soon as he shows, we can go.
Good.

04:17.023 --> 04:18.456
Cheer up, Frank.

04:18.458 --> 04:20.408
At least there's an open bar.

04:20.410 --> 04:23.545
Finally, someone I wouldn't mind
having a drink with.

04:23.547 --> 04:24.663
Hey!

04:25.247 --> 04:26.531
Aw.
You do this

04:26.533 --> 04:28.049
all the time.
What's your secret

04:28.051 --> 04:30.135
to surviving these things, Tony?
You just got

04:30.137 --> 04:32.537
to look at it
as part of the workday,

04:32.539 --> 04:35.473
the fun part with free booze
and food. Hiya, Garrett.

04:35.475 --> 04:36.641
Evening, Councilman.

04:36.643 --> 04:38.143
I hear Jimmy
Manning's retiring.

04:38.145 --> 04:41.513
Yeah, they're throwing quite a racket
for him uptown, I hear.

04:41.515 --> 04:43.481
Should get pretty wild.
You want to go?

04:43.483 --> 04:45.767
Well, being commissioner
kind of makes me

04:45.769 --> 04:48.103
a wet blanket at those things.
Miss 'em, though.

04:48.105 --> 04:50.855
Back in the old days, you were
always the last guy standing.

04:50.857 --> 04:52.240
You were always
the first one to leave,

04:52.242 --> 04:54.392
usually with the girl who
popped out of the cake.

04:54.394 --> 04:56.027
The mayor's new budget, Tony.
Mm.

04:56.029 --> 04:59.063
He's cutting my funding
for stress training.

04:59.065 --> 05:00.231
I saw that.
I put that

05:00.233 --> 05:02.951
program in place
when I came on as PC.

05:02.953 --> 05:04.002
It was part of the deal.

05:04.004 --> 05:06.121
Different times,
different mayor.

05:06.123 --> 05:08.906
This administration's all about austerity.
It's gonna be about

05:08.908 --> 05:11.710
damage control if the city isn't safe.
I get it.

05:11.712 --> 05:14.546
I used to carry a gold shield
myself, remember?

05:14.548 --> 05:16.381
Well, have it in your pocket
when the vote comes up.

05:16.383 --> 05:19.517
It's gonna come down
to three undecideds.

05:19.519 --> 05:21.102
Garcia, Vogel...

05:21.104 --> 05:23.805
and Tong--
we need all three.

05:23.807 --> 05:26.224
Well, Garcia's pro-cop.
So is Tong.

05:26.226 --> 05:28.109
Yeah, but the
mayor's people

05:28.111 --> 05:31.029
are working these guys hard, and
it's an election year for them.

05:31.031 --> 05:33.114
We need this one, Tony.

05:41.824 --> 05:43.408
Thanks for coming
back in, Kevin.

05:43.410 --> 05:46.294
Listen, I told you everything last night.
I got nothing more to say.

05:46.296 --> 05:48.963
Right, well, we heard that you
and Angela fought all the time.

05:48.965 --> 05:51.115
- Whatever. That bitch is crazy.
- Hey,

05:51.117 --> 05:52.217
watch your mouth.

05:52.219 --> 05:54.636
I ain't seen Angela in weeks.

05:54.638 --> 05:57.288
She told me she met
some big shot.

05:57.290 --> 05:58.690
I feel bad for him.

05:58.692 --> 05:59.641
Yeah, why's that?

05:59.643 --> 06:02.126
Angela likes to party.

06:02.128 --> 06:04.562
She's got a real mouth on her
and a serious temper.

06:04.564 --> 06:06.481
That why you
beat her up last night?

06:06.483 --> 06:08.483
For the hundredth time,
I wasn't with Angela last night.

06:08.485 --> 06:10.101
I saw the ambulance,
I checked it out--

06:10.103 --> 06:11.736
that ain't a crime.
You ought to know

06:11.738 --> 06:13.605
about crime, right, Kevin?
I mean, you got collars

06:13.607 --> 06:16.107
for breaking and entering,
assault, resisting arrest.

06:16.109 --> 06:17.609
Yeah.

06:17.611 --> 06:19.415
And that doesn't mean
I slapped her around last night.

06:19.440 --> 06:19.995
Come on.

06:19.996 --> 06:21.813
We recorded your voice
in the car last night.

06:21.815 --> 06:23.998
Intel's gonna match it
to the voice on the 911 tape,

06:24.000 --> 06:26.251
so why don't you do us all
a favor, stop wasting time

06:26.253 --> 06:27.702
and just give it up, all right?

06:27.704 --> 06:30.538
If Angela I.D.'d me for this,
I'd be in a cell right now.

06:30.540 --> 06:32.173
You got nothing and you know it.

06:32.958 --> 06:35.343
We'll see about that.

06:36.879 --> 06:38.263
Is that how you
do it, tough guy?

06:38.265 --> 06:40.164
You scare them so bad
they're afraid to complain?

06:40.166 --> 06:41.182
Is that it?

06:41.184 --> 06:42.717
Some girls ask for it, you know?

06:42.719 --> 06:45.270
Really?
Yeah, some even like it.

06:45.272 --> 06:47.806
What about you, Detective--
you like it?

06:50.342 --> 06:52.811
You like that, Kevin?!
Get her off me!

06:52.813 --> 06:55.396
Huh? You like that? Seems like you do!
Come on! Come on!

06:55.398 --> 06:56.865
What?!

06:56.867 --> 06:58.149
Come on.

06:58.151 --> 07:01.286
Not so fun
when they fight back, huh?

07:02.950 --> 07:06.950
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Blue Bloods 3x02 ♪</font>
